Title: Orthogonality criterion for banishing hydrino states from standard
  quantum mechanics
Authors: Antonio S. de Castro
Categories: hep-th quant-ph
Comments: 6 pages
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett.A369:380-383,2007
DOI: 10.1016/j.physleta.2007.05.006
\\
  Orthogonality criterion is used to shown in a very simple and general way
that anomalous bound-state solutions for the Coulomb potential (hydrino states)
do not exist as bona fide solutions of the Schr\"{o}dinger, Klein-Gordon and
Dirac equations.
